Use:
You need linux source, see https://github.com/notro/rpi-source/wiki
- sudo apt-get install git bc bison flex libssl-dev
- sudo chmod +x /usr/local/bin/rpi-source && /usr/local/bin/rpi-source -q --tag-update
- run rpi-source
When linux source is installed:
- update code (if necessary)
- run make
- run ./cp_modules_to_destination.sh
- add dtoverlay=rpi-dac to /boot/config.txt
- restart rpi
- run lsmod and make sure that it lists:
    snd_soc_pcm1794a,snd_soc_bcm2835_i2s,snd_soc_rpi_simple_soundcard
- make sure that aplay -l and arecord -l lists:
    sndrpirpidac [snd_rpi_rpi_dac], device 0: RPi-DAC HiFi pcm1794a-hifi-0 []
- try playback with:
    mplayer http://ice2.somafm.com/groovesalad-128-mp3
- try recording with (adjust parameters where needed):
    arecord -D hw:0,0 -d 100 -f S16_LE -r 44100 -c2 tmp.wav
